President Biden delivered a speech at the Tioga Marine Terminal in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, where he announced a $7 billion federal investment in clean hydrogen to power the economy. This investment is expected to attract $40 billion in private investment and create tens of thousands of good-paying jobs, with a focus on union labor. The president emphasized the importance of investing in industries of the future and transitioning to a clean energy future to combat climate change. He also highlighted the role of unions in building the middle class and reiterated his commitment to investing in American projects, workers, and products. Additionally, President Biden discussed the bipartisan infrastructure bill and its impact on job creation and economic growth. He expressed optimism about America's future and urged unity and cooperation to address the country's challenges.